    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><div n="1" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Ἀγαθῇ τύχῃ <supplied reason="lost">τῶν κυ</supplied>ρίων <lb n="2"/>Ἀσσκληπιάδης θεῷ <lb n="3"/>Ἀσσκληπιῷ εὐχαριστήρ<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied>ον </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Pro </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> vic</ab></div><div n="4" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>to</ab></div><div n="5" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>ria </ab></div><div n="6" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> do</ab></div><div n="7" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>mi</ab></div><div n="8" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>no</ab></div><div n="9" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>rum </ab></div><div n="10" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> no</ab></div><div n="11" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>stro</ab></div><div n="12" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/>rum </ab></div><div n="13" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> Aretes cau<lb break="no" n="2"/>sa dio <note>sic</note> Aescu<lb break="no" n="3"/>lapio Ascle<lb break="no" n="4"/>piades Ascle<lb break="no" n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">piadis filiu</supplied>s marm&amp;lt;o=A&amp;gt;rari<supplied reason="lost">us</supplied> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>Nicomed</abbr><ex>iensis</ex></expan> 
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Inschriftträger: shrine-shaped stele, with bust of Serapis in the pediment and a snake before a pine cone in the centre; text carved on the pediment&amp;apos;s frame, on the pilasters and on the pedestal. (B): IRT: Z. 5: marmorari[u]s. Fundstelle: found in the Sahel.</p>
            </div>
